On Sun, Oct 25, 2009 at 9:07 PM, David Schwarze <dschwarze(-at-)dfwair.net>wrote:

> I'm afraid it's not that simple.  The Vanagon 2.0 case does NOT match up
> properly to the 79 fan housing and tin.  I suppose it could be made to work
> with a BFH and lots of Permatex but it would be a kludge.  When I was faced
> with this situation, I took the Vanagon motor apart and put the rotating
> assembly into my '73 case.  Yes it's a lot more work but it will work
> perfectly and look factory.
